[[=]]
++ Junior Researcher Ariadne Cooper
[[/=]]

[[<]]

Dr. Cooper is obstinately my author avatar, except she has her shit significantly more together than I do by every metric. Currently --possibly eternally-- a Junior Researcher in the Department of Tactical Theology, Ariadne is an adept problem solver, a quick thinker, and possibly possessing absolutely no sense of humor. Dr. Cooper is in her early thirties, very short, and uses a cane to walk (which is really no one's business and she would prefer no one asked questions about it), with a strong academic background in world folklore, particularly in comparative mythology, proto Indo-European reconstruction, and nomadic oral traditions. While not housed at any specific site full time, her work often takes her to Site-89, Reliquary Area-27, and  Site-666.

